University of Central Florida: The University of Central Florida (UCF) is a public research university with its main campus in unincorporated Orange County, Florida.  It is part of the State University System of Florida. With 68,442 students as of the fall 2022 semester, UCF has the second-largest on-campus student body of any public university in the United States.
